alia are involved with rugby league as players, sport administrators, coaches, employees, club members, or volunteers. Karen Hardy of \"\" estimates this number could easily be quadrupled if wives, girlfriends, mothers, and other female family members who support male players were included. Participation is also increasing, with almost a thousand new female players taking up the sport between 2011 and 2012 for 5,801 total registered female players in 2012."}
