nel 4 chose to remain anonymous, with only Goss identifying himself. The airline says RPG only conducted their survey to unionise Ryanair pilots and issued a statement describing the documentary as \"based on nothing more than anonymous hearsay claims made by individuals whose identity was concealed, and/or by representatives of pilot unions of Ryanair's competitor airlines masquerading as a non-Ryanair Pilot Group\".\nRyanair claim Goss wrote to the airline saying he had no concerns about safety, stating \"We will not allow a Ryanair employee to defame our safety on national television just three weeks after he confirmed in writing to Ryanair that he had no concerns with safety and no reason to make any confidential safety report\". The airline further say they \"look forward to correcting Mr Goss's defamatory claims in court\".\nChannel 4 have previously stated an intent to defend the legal action against them."}
