her. Both survived. \nMr Justice Spencer identified Dennehy as a with , in which sexual pleasure is gained from the suffering of others. She wrote him a letter saying she had no remorse for the murders. The mother of two joins and as the only women to be given whole-life sentences in the UK, in which convicts are told they will never be released.\nThe sentencing follows a recent ruling by the court of appeal upholding the legality of whole life terms. The four defendants were jailed in Courtroom 2 of the Old Bailey, where on Wednesday Michael Adebolajo also received a whole life term for a terror attack which ."}
